  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Context Change:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Context change to different core on invocating an API will have an Overhead"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Example Use case:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We decided to move Module B to Core 1 to improve performance"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/10.%20Challenges%20in%20Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_UseCase.bmp?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_UseCase.bmp"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "So to call Module B in Core 1 from Module 0 there will be context change."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Context Change can be implemented in two ways"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Data driven invocation",
        "Event driven invocation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Both the implementation adds execution time overhead"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "On the caller side (notification / serialization, shared buffer handling)",
        "On the called core (worker execution, task scheduling, deserialization)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "Relocation decision",
      "content": "Relocation of an module should be done only when the module has an high execution time or small execution time but had to run more frequently In other words: There is not much sense in relocating a  small execution time which causes overhead that is larger"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2427144578/Context%20Challenge%20in%20Multicore.png?version=7&modificationDate=1663744084000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Context Challenge in Multicore.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Data Driven Invocation"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Module B in Core1 have an cyclic runnable which takes input value from shared memory process it and puts it back the output value to shared memory"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2427144578/Data%20Driven.png?version=3&modificationDate=1663740834000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Data Driven.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/10.%20Challenges%20in%20Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_Data_Driven.bmp?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_Data_Driven.bmp"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Event driven Invocation"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In this solution, an event will be set in another core which will activate an task and call the API in module B"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2427144578/Data%20Invocation%20Overview.png?version=7&modificationDate=1663740323000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Data Invocation Overview.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Note: in below diagram, we didn't show shared memory handling using spinlock"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/10.%20Challenges%20in%20Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_Event_Driven.bmp?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/10. Challenges in Multicore/Multicore_Context_Change_Event_Driven.bmp"
    }
  ],
